Put a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} on to boil for the pasta.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Trim the @courgette{1}. Use a #peeler{} to peel long ribbons down the length of the courgette, stopping at the spongy centre.

Zest and halve the @lemon{1/2}.

Once boiling, add the @rigatoni pasta{180%g} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

When ready, reserve some of the pasta water, then drain in a #colander{}.

Pop the pasta back into the pan, drizzle with @oil{}, and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat. Once hot, add the courgette ribbons and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Cook until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}, then stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Add the @baby spinach{100%g} a handful at a time and cook until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}. Transfer everything to a large #bowl{} and cover to keep warm.

Put your (now empty) frying pan back on medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Once the oil is hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{240%g} and shallot and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Stir in the @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and @reserved pasta water{100%ml}, then simmer until reduced by half, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Mix in the @creme fraiche{150%g} and heat through until piping hot, then season with @black pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Stir three quarters of the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} through your creamy sauce.

Add the cooked pasta and half the cooked green veg and stir well to combine. Simmer until everything's piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add a pinch of lemon zest and a squeeze of lemon juice. Taste and add more salt, pepper and lemon juice if needed. Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

Share the creamy pasta between your bowls and top with the remaining cooked green veg.

Finish with a sprinkle of the remaining hard Italian style cheese. Enjoy!